text.section:
The statewide voter registration list shall:
be the official voter registration list for the State;
contain the name and other information for every legally registered voter in the State;
allow each local board to obtain immediate electronic access to the information contained in the list;
be coordinated with other agency databases in the State;
be used to produce precinct registers for use in polling places on election day; and
include voting history information on a current basis for a period covering at least the 5 preceding years.

The State Administrator shall:
define, maintain, and administer the statewide voter registration list;
with the local boards, ensure the currency and accuracy of each individual voter's registration record;
instruct the local boards on:
processing voter registration applications and name and address changes;
entering voter registration information into the statewide voter registration list; and
removing from the statewide voter registration list information about voters who are no longer eligible to be registered voters; and
subject to relevant federal law and to regulations adopted by the State Board, establish and conduct a program to identify voters who have changed their addresses.
